
***
# Markdown Syntax User Guide 
(This page was written in Markdown.)

This guide provides an overview of Markdown syntax elements. Below are examples for creating the following in Markdown:
- Headings
- Table of Contents
- Tables
- Uploading images and files 
- eMail and YouTube Video Links



## How to Create Headings

# Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3
#### Heading 4
##### Heading 5
###### Heading 6



## How to Create a Table of Contents (ToC)

Here are two different templates for how to create a Table of Context using Markdown:
 
# My Topic Title
## My topic subtitle
Here comes my text. The next one is a set of steps:
1. Step 1.
2. Step 2....

# Table of Contents 
(**Syntax**: To create links to the headings of a ToC, separate spaces in the title with a dash (-).)
1. [My Topic Title](#My-Topic-Title)
2. [My topic subtitle](#my-topic-subtitle)



## How to Create a Table

Here are two different templates for how to create a table using Markdown:

| col1 | col2| col3 |
--- | --- | ---
| col1 text | col2 text | col3 text |



| Information type | Description |
 --- | ---
| Concept | Use it to provide conceptual information, answering the question "What is this?" |
| Task | Use it to provide instructional information, answering the question "How to do this?" |
| Reference | Use it to provide additional information, such as a table with reference values, or additional information |


## How to Upload Images and Files

1. Go to the code page of your project.
2. Choose Add File.
3. Navigate to the location of the file and upload it to your repository.
4. Copy the link to the file.

![D20 Dice Image](https://github.com/JenArmenta/writing-samples/blob/main/D20%20Image.png)

D20 Image

## How to Create a Mail Link

A link can point to a website or an email address.

**Syntax**:
Just like a regular web link, but start with *mailto*:

[linktext](*mailto*:email address)

**Result**: This link will allow the user to send an email directly to the email address:

[jenarmenta@gmail.com](mailto:jenarmenta@gmail.com)


## How to Create a Link to a YouTube Video

1. Go to the YouTube page with the video that you want to link.
2. Copy the video URL. The URL will look like this: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bTVIMt3XllM. You only need the last part OF THE URL: bTVIMt3XllM. 
3. Paste the last past of the URL into the code below where instructed:

<div align="left">
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PASTE URL HERE">
         <img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/PASTE URL HERE/0.jpg" style="width:100%;">
      </a>
</div>

**Example**: 

<div align="left">
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUBNt18RFbo">
         <img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/HUBNt18RFbo/0.jpg" style="width:100%;">
      </a>
</div>


